<p class="mb-4 text-xl"><strong>A Place Where a Diversity of Identities, ideas, and Experiences are Valued</strong></p>
<p class="mb-4 text-xl">Diversity is a source of strength, creativity, and innovation for UW&ndash;Madison. We value the contributions of each person and respect the profound ways their identity, culture, background, experience, status, abilities, and opinions enrich the university community. We commit ourselves to the pursuit of excellence in teaching, research, outreach, and diversity as inextricably linked goals. </p>

<p class="mb-4 text-xl"><strong>A Vibrant and Connected Postdoc Community </strong></p>
<p class="mb-4 text-xl">UW&ndash;Madison is one of the largest postdoctoral research training institutions in the U.S. training over 1,100 postdocs each year. Our postdoc community is 42% female and 53% international, and our postdocs train in 130 different departments from the arts and humanities to the biological, physical and social sciences. To ensure that the unique needs of the postdoc community are recognized, postdoc representatives are appointed to university shared governance committees. We also support a strong and long-standing postdoctoral association which organizes community building activities throughout the year including the Annual UW&ndash;Madison Postdoctoral Research Symposium in the fall, and the Celebration of Postdoc Excellence awards ceremony and dinner each spring.  </p>

<p class="mb-4 text-xl"><strong>Opportunities to Advance Your Career and Develop Professionally </strong></p>
<div class="px-16"><img class="max-w rounded overflow-hidden shadow-xl bg-whitep mb-8 md:float-right md:max-w-md md:ml-8" src="/img/uw-terrace.jpg" alt="Terrace"></div>

<p class="mb-4 text-xl">In addition to receiving mentored research training from world-class research leaders, UW&ndash;Madison postdocs also have free access to substantive professional development opportunities tailored to postdocs. We are fortunate to have three full-time staff dedicated to providing postdoc services within the Office of Postdoctoral Studies. This team offers individual career advising appointments, small group workshops, and employer visits to promote postdoc success in a diverse range of career paths. Recognizing the importance of professional skills development, the postdoc office also offers a course in scientific leadership, grant writing training and support, and regular workshops in critical skills such as conflict resolution and project management. Additional UW&ndash;Madison programs offer further postdoc-specific training in areas such as teaching, entrepreneurship and communication skills.   </p>

<p class="mb-4 text-xl"><strong>Support for Your Success and Wellbeing  </strong></p>
<p class="mb-4 text-xl">Postdocs are eligible to receive affordable comprehensive medical, prescription drug, dental and vision coverage, and generous paid time off including parental leave. We recognize that postdoc needs are different from other members of our community so the Office of Postdoctoral Studies provides confidential consultation and support to postdocs to help them navigate their postdoctoral training experience including any issues arising in their mentoring relationships. When personal or work-related concerns become difficult to manage, UW&ndash;Madison’s Employee Assistance Office also offers postdocs and their family members counseling and consultation at no cost. In these ways, we aim to ensure the success and wellbeing of every postdoc at the university.   </p>

